abstract: Dutch officials are demanding an investigation after the beating of the Netherlands' senior diplomat Onno Elderenbosch in his apartment in Moscow; Russian Foreign Ministry is trying to head off political fallout from attack by promising to detain the two assailants.

byline.original: By ANDREW ROTH and STEPHEN CASTLE
byline.contributor: Andrew Roth reported from Moscow, and Stephen Castle from London.

lead_paragraph: The Russian Foreign Ministry tried to head off any political fallout from the attack in the diplomat’s apartment by promising to detain the two assailants.

headline.main: Assault of Dutch Diplomat in Moscow Frays Ties Between Russia and the Netherlands
headline.print_headline: Assault of Dutch Diplomat Further Frays Ties Between Russia and the Netherlands
